---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Download KCode" description="Install KCode on Linux, macOS, or Windows (WSL). Multiple install methods available.">
  <section class="hero container">
    <h1>Install KCode</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      Get started in seconds. KCode runs on Linux, macOS, and Windows (via WSL).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="install-options">
      <div>
        <h3>Quick Install (recommended)</h3>
        <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://kulvex.ai/install.sh | bash</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>Homebrew (macOS / Linux)</h3>
        <pre><code>brew install astrolexis/tap/kcode</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>npm / bun</h3>
        <pre><code>npm install -g kcode
# or
bun install -g kcode</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>Binary Download</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          Download prebuilt binaries from the
          <a href="https://github.com/astrolexis/kcode/releases">GitHub Releases</a> page.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>From Source</h3>
        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/astrolexis/kcode.git
cd kcode
bun install
bun run build</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>System Requirements</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">KCode is lightweight but benefits from decent hardware for local model inference.</p>

    <table class="feature-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Component</th>
          <th>Minimum</th>
          <th>Recommended</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>OS</td>
          <td>Linux, macOS 13+, Windows 10+ (WSL2)</td>
          <td>Same</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Runtime</td>
          <td>Bun 1.0+ or Node.js 20+</td>
          <td>Bun 1.1+</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>RAM</td>
          <td>4 GB (cloud-only)</td>
          <td>16 GB+ (local models)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>GPU</td>
          <td>Not required (cloud mode)</td>
          <td>NVIDIA/AMD GPU with 8+ GB VRAM for local inference</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Disk</td>
          <td>200 MB (CLI only)</td>
          <td>10+ GB (with local models)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>First Run</h2>
    <div class="install-options">
      <div>
        <h3>1. Setup wizard</h3>
        <pre><code>kcode setup</code></pre>
        <p style="color: var(--text-muted);">Detects your hardware, downloads a recommended model, and configures your API keys.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>2. Start coding</h3>
        <pre><code>cd your-project
kcode</code></pre>
        <p style="color: var(--text-muted);">Launch the interactive terminal UI and start working with AI in your codebase.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
